Knowing someone that was a victim of the program does not mean you know more. Are you saying all the files of the entire program are given to great nephews of victims? You're full of it. 

Read the book. If reading is too difficult, the audio book is on YouTube.

@tomkluding The only person who's ever published the facts is MM, but his name can't even be written here.
  The point is a simple one -
"All the world's a stage..."

@IvorLongshaft yeah I did read the book. And his entire proof for the book is trust me bro. Or his sources are people and their qualifications are trust me bro. Also, I think it's funny that you want to talk about how I know less about it than other people when I've known someone who was actually involved in it. That actually had news media under Canada and Americas laws of freedom of information act be able to get that information and I've actually read those files. That you think you know more than me because you read a book whose guys only sources are trust me bro. And that guy said trust him bro. 

Just because I'd rather focus on the actual victims and not the pretend victims or use it as an excuse to why Charles Manson did what he did. Because I understand that cults and evil cult leaders have literally been around since the beginning of f****** human history. Doesn't mean I didn't read the book. Just because I actually had a critical interpretation of it and didn't swallow everything he said like it was. The tastiest tasty s*** I've ever put in my mouth doesn't mean doesn't mean I didn't read the book. 

Especially considering all the people who actually knew Charles Manson were involved in the cult have denounced this book as complete and utter nonsense. But let me guess you know more than them too. Because you know more than everything cuz you believe a book that's only sources. Trust me bro or trust him bro. Oh the confidence of the perpetually wrong.
